sm, especially the historiography of law and religion in England.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 28. Mrz 2024) 7aLITERARY CRITICISM / General.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertACUP Complete eBook-Package Pre-2010z978311127416408iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertACUP Upgrade eBook-Package pre 2010z978311127724008iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertMcGill-Queen's UP Complete eBook-Package Pre-2000z978311141762240uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780773567771423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780773567771/original  a978-3-11-127416-4  ACUP Complete eBook-Package Pre-2010b2010  a978-3-11-127724-0  ACUP Upgrade eBook-Package pre 2010b2010  a978-3-11-141762-2  McGill-Queen's UP Complete eBook-Package Pre-2000b2000  aGBV-deGruyter-alles